summary: This document appears to be a file directory or index listing numerous image files (JPG, TIF) and some Photoshop files (PSD) associated with the Epstein case. The filenames suggest the images may include personal photographs, possibly from Epstein's properties or travels, as indicated by folder names like 'Midnight Express', 'LSJ rock clearing', 'GM ankle/Joshua', 'Maya carnival', and 'LSJ painted rooms'. The document includes notations that some items were not scanned and one entry marked 'CSAM NOT SCANNED'.
keyFacts: The document is an index of image files (JPG, TIF) and Photoshop files (PSD) seized or collected in the Epstein investigation.
Folder names like 'Midnight Express', 'LSJ rock clearing', 'GM ankle/Joshua', 'Maya carnival', and 'LSJ painted rooms' suggest categorization of personal or property-related photographs.
One entry is explicitly marked 'CSAM NOT SCANNED', indicating the presence of material suspected to be Child Sexual Abuse Material that was not digitized in this set.
Multiple entries state 'ITEM WAS NOT SCANNED DESCRIPTION', indicating portions of the evidence were not imaged or are missing from this digital record.
The repetitive file naming structure (e.g., DSCFxxxx_1.TIF, CIMGxxxx.JPG) suggests a systematic, large-scale seizure of digital media.
